# CCO canonical GPU pin — runtime/gpu.config  (sourced by runtime/start.sh).
#
# The GPU SKU is part of the locked "model": a speedup is only meaningful against the champion on
# IDENTICAL hardware. The canonical rerun MUST run on this exact SKU; changing it is a vN -> vN+1
# competition reset. Roofline peaks for the SKU live in benchmark.py (_KNOWN_GPUS) and are
# reported-only — they do NOT enter the champion-relative score.
#
# v1: the canonical SKU is the pinned GPU used for scored reruns. Until a canonical SKU is fixed,
# this is pinned to the CCO development box.

CCO_GPU_NAME="NVIDIA GeForce RTX 5070 Ti"   # exact string from `nvidia-smi --query-gpu=name`
CCO_GPU_CC="12.0"                            # compute capability major.minor (torch.cuda)
CCO_GPU_INDEX="0"                            # GPU the canonical rerun binds to (exclusive)

# Optional fixed clocks for timing stability (operator-provided; needs a privileged container).
# Leave unset to skip clock locking.
# CCO_LOCK_GRAPHICS_CLOCK="2400"
# CCO_LOCK_MEMORY_CLOCK="14001"
